[zero_shot][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][mmlu] sample 13/100 done id=mmlu_test_1519 prediction="Question: What is a web proxy?\n\nChoices:\nA. A piece of software that intercepts and possibly modifies requests (and responses) between a web browser and web server\nB. An agent that makes decisions on the client's behalf when interacting with web applications\nC. A piece of software that makes a web application look like a standalone application, making it easier to test\nD. A simulator for the web, for use when off-line\n\nReasoning:\n\n1. A web proxy is a piece of software that intercepts and possibly modifies requests (and responses) between a web browser and web server. This means that it acts as a middleman between the two, allowing the browser to communicate with the server without having to do so directly.\n\n2. Web proxies are often used for security purposes, as they can help protect users from malicious websites and prevent them from being redirected to dangerous sites.\n\n3. Web proxies can also be used for testing purposes, as they allow developers to simulate different scenarios and test their applications without having to actually run them on a real web server.\n\n4. Web proxies can also be used for" gold='A' correct=False
