[zero_shot][tinyllama_1_1b_chat][mmlu] sample 49/100 done id=mmlu_test_5925 prediction='Question: Which of the following inferences about sources of political authority in the period circa 600 B.C.E.–600 C.E. Is supported by the passage?\n\nA. Rulers derived legitimacy for their rule by their sponsorship of religion and chief priests.\n\nB. Rulers were limited in their political authority by powerful religious figures.\n\nC. Rulers derived legitimacy for their rule through victories over foreign peoples.\n\nD. Rulers derived legitimacy for their rule through the consent of those they governed.\n\nThe passage supports the inference that rulers derived legitimacy for their rule through their sponsorship of religion and chief priests. The passage states that rulers held me in high honor and dignity and at court and in kingdom after kingdom, place after place, gave me authority and power for divine services of every sort. This implies that rulers were supported by religious figures, who were seen as legitimate authorities in the eyes of the people. Additionally, the passage states that in kingdom after kingdom, place after place, many divine services were performed in magnificence and many Warharan fires' gold='A' correct=False
